Polysilicon Spot Prices Dropped 3.5% Last Week, BNEF Data Shows

-- B y   M a r c   R o c a
-- 
2011-11-29T13:18:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-29/polysilicon-spot-prices-dropped-3-5-last-week-bnef-data-shows.html
     Nov. 29 (Bloomberg) --  Polysilicon , the raw material used
to make most solar panels, dropped 3.5 percent last week,
accelerating week-on-week, Bloomberg New Energy Finance data
shows.  The average spot price of a kilogram fell to $28.83 last
week from $29.88 a week earlier, the London-based research group
said today. Prices have been falling since September and are
down almost 62 percent this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marc Roca in London at 
